What occurred during the same time as the beginning of the decline of women in computer science?
The share of women in computer science started falling at roughly the same moment when personal computers started showing up in U.S. homes in significant numbers.

Why does it matter that males had been playing on computers growing up?

In the 1990s, researcher Jane Margolis interviewed hundreds of computer science students at Carnegie Mellon University, 
Which had one of the top programs in the country. She found that families were much more likely to buy computers for boys than for girls â€” even when their girls were really interested in computers.
This was a big deal when those kids got to college. As personal computers became more common, computer science professors increasingly assumed that their students had grown up playing with computers at home.


When are diversity efforts most successful?
Successful diversity efforts hinge on leadership commitment, fostering an inclusive culture, diverse representation, continuous education, measuring progress, 
Supporting employee groups, and revising policies for equity. Integration into the organizational culture, rather than a standalone initiative, is key.

Why do diverse companies perform better?

Diverse companies perform better because they bring in varied perspectives for innovative solutions. 
Access a wider talent pool, make better decisions, connect effectively with diverse markets, boost employee engagement, and mitigate risks by considering various viewpoints.

Give an example of how a diverse company can serve a diverse user base or vise-versa.

A diverse team creating a language translation app can ensure accurate translations by understanding cultural nuances and diverse languages, catering to various user needs while avoiding unintentional offense.


